verbose_text: In addition, in mock and ICAM-5-Deltacp transfected neurons, alpha-actinin immunoreactivity formed clusters, which often located within spine heads (XREF_FIG); while full-length ICAM-5 transfection was able to prevent the clustering of alpha-actinin (XREF_FIG).
evidence: ICAM-5 transfection was able to prevent the clustering of alpha-actinin
